ComicInfo.Summary: There are two things you need to know about the man named Mister Coble. First, he's the head of the British Ministry of Objective Sciences, the branch of the Empire's government that deals with so-called "supernatural" or "spiritual" matters... and by "deal with," we mean "terminate." Second, he's actually traveled back to 1893 from the year 2006 for one reason alone: to stop the Mythstalkers. The Labyrinth, Part Four of Four, "What Your People Call Labyrinth, My People Call Maze" In the Labyrinth of Crete, the Mythstalkers found far more Minotaur than they expected... and the only one left conscious is the retired army Colonel, Augustus Durant. How can one old man defeat a trio of man-killers? And assuming he does, there's still the matter of getting a live Minotaur back to London. That's London... where Mister Coble waits for their return.
